# ProjectManager protocol — Spine

**Dashboard:** http://localhost:5190 (when PM service is running)

## Every agent MUST check in when starting and finishing work

```bash
# Starting
npm run pm:checkin -- --agent <id> --role <role> --status in_progress --task <TASK-ID> --message "Starting …"

# Completed
npm run pm:checkin -- --agent <id> --role <role> --status completed --task <TASK-ID> --message "Done …" --deliverable <path>

# Blocked
npm run pm:checkin -- --agent <id> --role <role> --status blocked --task <TASK-ID> --message "Blocked: reason"
```

Set `PM_URL=http://localhost:5190` if not default.

## QA agents MUST evidence test runs

```bash
npm run pm:qa
# or run configured QA command from pm.config.json
```

Do not claim "tests pass" without evidenced run in the same turn.

## PO / PM (main agent)

- Post milestones: `curl -X POST http://localhost:5190/api/events -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"eventType":"milestone","title":"…","source":"po"}'`
- User reviews live dashboard — updates via SSE without refresh.

## Source of truth

Backlog and gates live in `todo/` markdown. PM derives display state from those files — do not treat external ALM as canonical.
